## API methods

### 1. `log()` — one event

Best for one-off process events, coding/imputation notes, manual review routing, and step-completion messages emitted inline.

```python
logger.log(
    *,
    event_type,           # required
    message,              # required
    rule_name=None,
    response_id=None,
    case_id=None,
    variable_name=None,
)
```

Returns `None`.

| Parameter | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `event_type` | Yes | Event category, e.g. `coding`, `imputation`, `validation`, `review`, `manual_intervention`. Helps downstream filtering/grouping. |
| `message` | Yes | Human-readable description of what happened. |
| `rule_name` | No | Named business/process rule (free text, not registry-controlled), e.g. `ethnic_group_coding_v1`. |
| `response_id` | No | Record identifier, e.g. `person_nbr` or `dwell_nbr`. Optional because some events are task-level rather than row-level. |
| `case_id` | No | Case identifier (e.g. Salesforce), when available. |
| `variable_name` | No | Variable involved, e.g. `i_age`, `ethnic_group`. Use when the event is tied to one variable. |

```python
logger.log(
    event_type="coding",
    message="Applied ethnic group coding rules successfully",
    rule_name="ethnic_group_coding_v1",
    response_id="P12345",
    case_id="500Mp00000d56UCIAY",
    variable_name="ethnic_group",
)
```

---

### 2. `log_dataframe()` — bulk logging from a Spark DataFrame

Best when each row of a DataFrame represents one event (row-level imputation outcomes, manual-review results, bulk processing notes).

```python
logger.log_dataframe(
    df,                            # required
    *,
    event_type,                    # required
    rule_name=None,
    rule_name_column=None,
    message=None,
    message_column=None,
    response_id_column,            # required
    case_id_column=None,
    collection_instance_id_column=None,
    variable_name=None,
    variable_name_column=None,
)
```

**Returns** the number of records appended to the buffer (`int`); `0` if the DataFrame is empty.

> **Driver-memory safety limit.** This method collects rows to the driver. If the DataFrame has more than **100,000 rows** it raises `ValueError`. Filter or batch before calling.

**Required:**

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `df` | DataFrame with one row per event. |
| `event_type` | Event category applied to every row. |
| `response_id_column` | Column holding the response ID for each row (e.g. `"person_nbr"`). |
| `message` *or* `message_column` | Exactly one must be supplied — every event needs a message. |

**Per-row fields (DataFrame columns):**

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `message_column` | Per-row message text. |
| `rule_name_column` | Per-row rule/process name. |
| `case_id_column` | Per-row case IDs. |
| `collection_instance_id_column` | Per-row collection instance IDs; falls back to context if omitted. |
| `variable_name_column` | Per-row variable names (use when the DataFrame spans multiple variables). |

**Constant fields (applied to every row):**

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `message` | Constant message for all rows. |
| `rule_name` | Constant rule name for all rows. |
| `variable_name` | Constant variable name for all rows. |

**Mutual exclusivity** — passing both of a pair raises `ValueError`:
- `message` and `message_column` (and supplying *neither* also raises)
- `rule_name` and `rule_name_column`
- `variable_name` and `variable_name_column`

A missing `response_id_column`, or any named column not present in the DataFrame, also raises `ValueError`.

**Shape A — constant message and rule name:**

```python
logger.log_dataframe(
    df_imputed,
    event_type="imputation",
    rule_name="dob_imputation_v1",
    message="DOB imputed using age distribution",
    response_id_column="person_nbr",
    case_id_column="i_id",
    variable_name="i_dob_year",
)
```

**Shape B — per-row message:**

```python
logger.log_dataframe(
    df_events,
    event_type="review",
    message_column="event_message",
    response_id_column="person_nbr",
    case_id_column="i_id",
)
```

**Shape C — per-row message and rule name:**

```python
logger.log_dataframe(
    df_events,
    event_type="review",
    message_column="event_message",
    rule_name_column="rule_applied",
    response_id_column="person_nbr",
    case_id_column="i_id",
    variable_name_column="variable_name",
    collection_instance_id_column="collectionInstance",
)
```

**Shape D — per-row collection instance override:**

```python
logger.log_dataframe(
    df_events,
    event_type="coding",
    message_column="msg",
    response_id_column="person_nbr",
    collection_instance_id_column="collectionInstance",
)
```

